George Augustus Hunter Vanderspar (22 October 1858 – 23 May 1940) was an English cricketer. Born at Galle in British Ceylon, Vanderspar was a right-handed batsman and a right-arm fast-medium underarm bowler.
He made one appearance in first-class cricket for the Marylebone Cricket Club (MCC) against Kent in 1893 at Lord's. He batted once in the match, scoring 7 runs in the MCC's first-innings, before he was dismissed by Alec Hearne. The match ended in a victory for the MCC by an innings and 21 runs.He died at Bournemouth, Hampshire on 23 May 1940.
